 \begin{remark}[Restart Semantics]\label{rem:independent_restart}
 If signer~$i$ obtains $\bot$ from iterative rejection sampling, a fresh signing attempt is required. Because the challenge $c = H_2(w, m, L, \mathsf{ep}, D_{\mathsf{ep}})$ depends on the aggregate commitment $w = \sum_j w_j$, signer~$i$ cannot simply resample $\bvec{y}_i$ while keeping the other commitments fixed: changing $w_i$ would change~$w$ and therefore invalidate the challenge. Consequently, \emph{all signers must discard their current state and restart from Round~1 with fresh randomness}.
 
